## 2026-04-23 (Week 2 Mon/Tue + CORS fix + PR #1 merged to main)

### Shipped to production
- **PR #1 merged** → commit `287b1cc` → Vercel deploy on `main` → **`www.mdeai.co` now serves the chat-central canvas** (was the old `Index` marketing page). Verified: production bundle contains `ChatCanvas`, `apartment_save_counts` RPC name, "What are you looking for" welcome headline, "Ask about rentals" placeholder. End-to-end POST from `Origin: https://www.mdeai.co` returns 200 streaming SSE with 10 Laureles listings + phase events.

### `fix(cors)` — unblocks every browser POST to edge functions
- **`supabase/functions/_shared/http.ts`** — `getCorsHeaders(req)` was missing `Access-Control-Allow-Methods`. Browsers send `OPTIONS` preflight with `Access-Control-Request-Method: POST`, see no `Allow-Methods` in response, silently abort the follow-up POST. Server logs showed `OPTIONS 204` with no matching POST — every anon chat send failed with "Failed to get response."
- Added `Access-Control-Allow-Methods: POST, GET, OPTIONS`, added `x-anon-session-id` to `Allow-Headers` (so the 3-msg anon gate doesn't trip a second preflight failure), added `Access-Control-Max-Age: 86400` + `Vary: Origin` for Cloudflare/browser cache correctness.
- **All 10 edge functions redeployed** on `zkwcbyxiwklihegjhuql` (ai-chat, rentals, ai-router, ai-search, ai-trip-planner, ai-optimize-route, ai-suggest-collections, google-directions, rules-engine, p1-crm).

### Week 2 Tue — save + add-to-trip + social proof
- **New RPC** `public.apartment_save_counts(apartment_ids uuid[])` → migration `supabase/migrations/20260424120000_apartment_save_counts_rpc.sql`. `SECURITY DEFINER`; returns `(apartment_id, save_count)` only (no user_id leakage). Granted to `anon, authenticated`.
- **`src/hooks/useChatActions.ts`** — owns `savedIds`, `saveCounts`, `trips`; exposes `toggleSave` (optimistic w/ rollback), `addToTrip`, `createTripAndAdd`, `fetchSaveCounts`. Anon users get a friendly sign-in toast instead of RLS errors.
- **`src/components/chat/AddToTripModal.tsx`** — pick-existing or create-new flow. New-trip form enforces `trips.start_date` / `end_date` NOT NULL and drops the listing in as the first `trip_items` row.
- **`EmbeddedListings.tsx`** now owns the modal + fires the save-count RPC per batch of listings.
- **`RentalCardInline.tsx`** renders a rose-tinted **"Saved by N nomads"** badge when `save_count > 0` (social proof moat).

### Week 2 Mon — context chips + `session_data` persistence
- **`src/components/chat/ChatContextChips.tsx`** — four popover-backed chips above the message list: 📍 neighborhood · 📅 dates · 👥 travelers · 💰 budget. Clear-all button when any chip is set.
- **`src/hooks/useChat.ts`** — hydrates chips from `conversations.session_data.chat_context` on `selectConversation`; writes-through to Postgres on every edit; seeds `session_data` on brand-new conversations so pre-first-message chip edits aren't lost; sends `sessionData` on every `ai-chat` POST.
- **`src/types/chat.ts`** — `ChatContext` + `EMPTY_CHAT_CONTEXT` + `hasChatContext()` typed; `Conversation.session_data` typed.
- **`supabase/functions/ai-chat/index.ts`** — `sessionDataSchema` (strict Zod) + `sessionContextBlock()` injected into the system prompt so Gemini inherits chip values on the next tool call ("inherit unless user's latest message overrides"). Deployed v37 → v38 after CORS fix.

